# C# control flow braces

In C# (including Unity `Editor/` and `Modules/`), **never** use single-statement `if` / `else` / `for` / `foreach` / `while` **without** curly braces.

- Even when the body is **one line** (e.g. `return;`, `continue;`, one assignment), wrap it in `{ }`.
- Applies to new code and edits in this repo; match this style when touching existing blocks nearby.

```csharp
// Bad
if (x == null)
    return;

// Good
if (x == null)
{
    return;
}
```
